istered methods, which sounds useful. I should also consider adding a method echo. The ConstructedByFunction method records and might benefit from a default constructor. It could be helpful to implement a queryAllPublicMethods feature since the native config schema supports methods with invocation. I wonder if I need to include a user-code-filter and possibly a test package. I'll have to check on that!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_mCVqBZ6FQTNqpzNeQeZNjqTR|fc_07b6f25cda7d0cab0169f10853f84881949348a74a622219ca", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/user-code-filter.json", "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 735, "output": 1657, "cacheRead": 34304, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36696, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777403961152, "responseId": "resp_07b6f25cda7d0cab0169f10839cc8c8194960e11cb415f75ae"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_mCVqBZ6FQTNqpzNeQeZNjqTR|fc_07b6f25cda7d0cab0169f10853f84881949348a74a622219ca", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"rules\": [\n    {\n      \"excludeClasses\": \"**\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"includeClasses\": \"org.mozilla.**\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777403988391}]}
