[assistant] Fixed and committed the `SecurityManager` incompatibility.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Commit:
[assistant] - `a9505a269 Handle Rhino FunctionObject fallback without SecurityManager`
[assistant] 
[assistant] What changed:
[assistant] - `FunctionObjectTest.definesFunctionPropertiesWhenDeclaredMemberAccessIsDenied()` now:
[assistant]   - Uses the `SecurityManager` path when supported.
[assistant]   - Falls back on newer JVMs where `System.setSecurityManager(...)` throws `UnsupportedOperationException`.
[assistant]   - Restores Rhino’s `FunctionObject.sawSecurityException` state after the test.
[assistant] - Added native-image reflection config for `org.mozilla.javascript.FunctionObject.sawSecurityException`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not rerun the Gradle test locally, per the original instruction not to compile/run tests.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Still present as unrelated untracked content:
